        <div class="grid_12">
            <div class="x6">
                <p>Welcome to Bankview! Being a mature neighbourhood has its benefits. Bankview has had time to grow and thrive to become well established with all the necessary amenities to live a comfortable life. It’s one of the many reasons homeowners flock to this lovely neighbourhood. Bankview is also close to nature, so residents live a very active lifestyle, biking, walking and running. It’s also conveniently close to downtown Calgary. The neighbourhood lies on elevated land, giving residents panoramic views of downtown Calgary.</p>
                <p>Bankview is ideal for young people and those who look forward to leading an active, inner-city lifestyle. In fact, most of the community is made up of students, young families, and working professionals.</p>
                <p>If you love architecture and old buildings, you will love walking through and exploring this gorgeous place that has a history dating back to the 50s. The houses here are a mix of modern and traditional, and there is something for everyone.</p>
                <p>17th Avenue SW, 26th Avenue SW, 14th Street SW, and 19th Street SW form Bankview’s north, south, east, and west borders.</p>
                <p>The Bankview Community Association believes in inclusion and diversity and ensures it represents the interests of all the community’s residents.</p>
