            <div class="x6 last">
                <div>
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Parks &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>As a resident of Bankview, you will have access to a wide variety of parks spread across the community.</p>
                    <p><strong>Buckmaster Park</strong> on 21 Avenue SW has a basketball court, a trail, and a community garden.</p>
                    <p><strong>18a St SW Playground</strong> is a modern playground fitted with age-appropriate playground equipment for younger children.</p>
                    <p>There is the <strong>Bankview Off-Leash Area</strong> on 23 Avenue SW for your furry family members.</p>
                    <p>The <strong>Bankview Community Association</strong> has a sports field, tennis courts, and a basketball court for older children and families.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Shopping &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Located between 2nd Street SW and 16th Avenue SW is the sprawling 17th Avenue retail and entertainment district – home to hundreds of shops, nightclubs, bars, restaurants, and services. Set in a vibrant outdoor environment and spread over 13 blocks, this is the most happening area of Bankview.</p>
                    <p>There is always something exciting happening on 17th Avenue – and there’s invariably a brand new restaurant, a performance, or a new pub to check out. In short, there’s never a dull day or weekend in Bankview, thanks to 17th Avenue.</p>
                    <p>Marda Loop is a quick car drive away and another shopping haven for shoppers.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Fitness &mdash;</h3>
                    <p><strong>League</strong> is a fitness center on 17 Avenue SW offering yoga, HIIT programs, and spin classes. There is free street parking available in the area before 9 am and after 6 pm.</p>
                    <p>Whether you want to build muscle, improve posture, achieve a toned body, or save time, a personal trainer from <strong>Amped Advantage</strong> on 17th Avenue SW can help. All it takes is 20 minutes twice a week.</p>
                    <p><strong>Revive Lifestyle Fitness</strong> is a gym on 14 Street SW with great staff, excellent coaches, and high-intensity workouts. You can choose between online and offline classes.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Restaurants and bars &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Bankview’s residents have plenty of options when it comes to restaurants and bars. The ones closest to the community are:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Lately Lounge – cocktail bar</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Tropical on 17th and Chilitos Taberna – Mexican restaurants</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">YYC Pasta Bar</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Jamesons Pub</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Las Canarias – Spanish bar and eatery</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Watchman’s Pub & Eatery – Karaoke bar</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
