        <h2>FAQs about Bankview Real Estate and Neighborhood</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <h3>Where is the best place to shop?</h3>
                <p>17th Avenue SW is the best shopping destination for all your daily requirements. From clothing, jewelry, and home décor to electronics and wines, spirits, and beers – you will find it all at 17th Avenue. Services available here include banks, travel, salons and spas, and health and professional services.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>Is there a community garden?</h3>
                <p>The Bankview Community Association has a community garden formed by the residents. The garden helps those with limited space to grow their food, and residents can grow their fruit and vegetables here.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>How will I get about? Is there public transport?</h3>
                <p>Bankview is one of the most walkable neighbourhoods in Calgary, and you can complete several types of errands on foot. The neighbourhood is bikeable, and biking is convenient in most areas. Bankview has an excellent public transport system with at least three bus lines passing through the community.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>Where to buy groceries?</h3>
                <p>Several grocery and convenience stores dot the neighbourhood. Urban Fare on 17th Avenue is a large, well-stocked grocery, pharmacy, and convenience store a couple of minutes away from the community.</p>
                <p>If you require a specialty store, Tiba Grocery and Convenience and Kalamata is the place for Mediterranean and European foods.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>Which is the closest library?</h3>
                <p>The Giuffre Family Library on 14th Street SW is the closest library and the perfect place to spend an afternoon browsing or reading books. As well as offering books to its members, the library also hosts some fantastic programs like reading clubs during the summer months.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
